  <main class="wrap">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: February 16, 2026</p>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p>SpaceX Countdown is an independent app that provides launch countdowns, launch history, widgets, notifications, and optional premium Starlink features.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
      <p>We do not require account sign-up and do not collect personal profile data by default.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Launch and satellite data is fetched from public APIs.</li>
        <li>Cached app data is stored locally on your device for performance and offline fallback.</li>
        <li>No third-party analytics SDK is included in the MVP release.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>3. Notifications</h2>
      <p>If you enable launch alerts, notification scheduling data is stored locally on your device. You can disable notifications at any time in iOS Settings.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>4. In-App Purchases</h2>
      <p>Premium purchases are processed by Apple through StoreKit. We do not receive or store your payment card details.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal data. Data displayed in the app is sourced from public launch/satellite providers.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>Cached launch and Starlink data remains on your device until replaced by newer refreshes, app deletion, or system cleanup.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>7. Children’s Privacy</h2>
      <p>The app is not directed to children under 13 and does not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy periodically. The “Last updated” date above reflects the latest revision.</p>
    </section>

